ipriani.com/locations/los-angeles.php | title = Cipriani Beverly Hills | work = cipriani.com | access-date = 26 October 2010 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101024032337/http://www.cipriani.com/locations/los-angeles.php | archive-date = 24 October 2010 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n<ref name=cipriani-portocervo>{{cite web | url = http://www.cipriani.com/locations/porto-cervo.php | title = Cipriani Porto Cervo | work = cipriani.com | access-date = 26 October 2010 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101029080501/http://cipriani.com/locations/porto-cervo.php | archive-date = 29 October 2010 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n<ref name=cipriani-hongkong>{{cite web  | url = http://www.cipriani.com/locations/hong-kong.php  | title = Cipriani Hong Kong  | work = cipriani.com  | access-date = 26 October 2010  | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101029084640/http://cipriani.com/locations/hong-kong.php  | archive-date = 29 October 2010  | url-status = dead  }}</ref>\n<ref name=cipriani-miami>{{cite web | url = http://www.ciprianimiami.com/ | title = Cipriani Miami | format = dead link? | work = ciprianimiami.com }}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.cipriani.com/ cipriani.com]\n\n[[Category:Hotel and leisure companies of Luxembourg]]\n[[Category:Privately held companies of Luxembourg]]\n[[Category:Restaurants in Manhattan]]\n[[Category:Nightclubs in Manhattan]]\n[[Category:Restaurants in London]]\n[[Category:Restaurants in Italy]]\n[[Category:Restaurants established in 1931]]\n[[Category:1931 establishments in Italy]]\n[[Category:Italian restaurants]]\n", "name_user": "Gotitbro", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cipriani_S.A."}
{"title_page": "Bhairavi Prakash", "text_new": "'''Bhairavi Prakash''' is a work and [[Organizational behavior|organisational]] [[psychologist]] and the founder of The Mithra Trust.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Venkatraman|first=Janane|url=https://www.thehindu.com/life-and-style/mithra-on-promoting-mental-health-on-college-campuses/article25068796.ece|title=Taking it online: fostering mental health on college campuses|date=2018-09-28|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-25|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/hermindmatters-redefining-mental-health-new-moms-going-back-work-116830|website=www.thenewsminute.com|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref>\u00a0<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asianscientist.com/2018/08/features/artificial-intelligence-mental-health/|title=Artificial Intelligence and Mental Health|last=Asian Scientist|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> She lives in [[Chennai]], [[India]].\n\n== Biography ==\nBhairavi was born in Chennai to Bharathi and Ravi Prakash. She completed her schooling at [[Sishya School|Sishya]], Chennai, and pursued her bachelor's degree in Psychology at the [[Women's Christian College, Chennai|Women's Christian College]], Chennai. She went on to complete her master's in work and organisational psychology at the [[University of Nottingham]] [[Business school|Business School]]. She was a [[Social innovation|Social Innovation]] Management Fellow at the Amani Institute from 2018 to 2019.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://amaniinstitute.org/profile/bhairavi-prakash/|title=Bhairavi Prakash \u2013 Amani Institute|website=amaniinstitute.org|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nIn the past, Bhairavi worked as a consultant with Totus Consulting, Chennai, where the work she did focusing on coaching and leadership development projects won awards.<ref name=\":0\" /> Bhairavi set up India's first for-profit school-mental health program.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Social Entrepreneurship ==\nBhairavi founded The Mithra Trust in September 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Adlakha|first=Nidhi|url=https://www.thehindu.com/life-and-style/what-mental-health-experts-say/article31185530.ece|title=COVID-19 lockdown: What mental health experts say|date=2020-03-27|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-25|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://projectkal.org/our-voice/2020/1/13/social-entrepreneur-spotlight|title=Social Entrepreneur Spotlight|website=Project Kal|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref> The trust operates as a non-profit that works with various communities on positive mental health through making information available through workshops, tools, and allied services.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.edexlive.com/happening/2019/oct/31/feeling-meh-this-self-help-kit-will-coach-you-on-what-to-say-when-8845.html|title=Feeling meh? This self-help kit will coach you on what to say when|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref> Through The Mithra Trust, Bhairavi created \u201cThe Meh Kit\u201d which serves as a [[self-help]] kit to help people coping with [[Depression (mood)|depression]].<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite news|last=Lazarus|first=Susanna Myrtle|url=https://www.thehindu.com/sci-tech/technology/internet/beat-the-blues-with-these-helpful-kits/article29416688.ece|title=Beat the blues with these helpful kits|date=2019-09-14|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-25|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n<br />\n\n[[Category:Indian social entrepreneurs]]\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Social entrepreneurs]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian businesswomen]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Indian businesswomen by state or union territory]]\n[[Category:Mental health by country]]\n[[Category:Mental health activists]]\n[[Category:Psychologists by nationality]]\n[[Category:Indian psychologists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "Bhairavi Prakash is a work and [[Organizational behavior|organisational]] [[psychologist]] and the founder of The Mithra Trust.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Venkatraman|first=Janane|url=https://www.thehindu.com/life-and-style/mithra-on-promoting-mental-health-on-college-campuses/article25068796.ece|title=Taking it online: fostering mental health on college campuses|date=2018-09-28|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-25|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/hermindmatters-redefining-mental-health-new-moms-going-back-work-116830|website=www.thenewsminute.com|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref>\u00a0<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asianscientist.com/2018/08/features/artificial-intelligence-mental-health/|title=Artificial Intelligence and Mental Health|last=Asian Scientist|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> She lives in [[Chennai]], [[India]]. \n\n== Biography ==\nBhairavi was born in Chennai to Bharathi and Ravi Prakash. She completed her schooling at [[Sishya School|Sishya]], Chennai, and pursued her bachelor\u2019s degree in Psychology at the [[Women's Christian College, Chennai|Women\u2019s Christian College]], Chennai. She went on to complete her master\u2019s in work and organisational psychology at the [[University of Nottingham]] [[Business school|Business School]]. She was a [[Social innovation|Social Innovation]] Management Fellow at the Amani Institute from 2018 to 2019.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://amaniinstitute.org/profile/bhairavi-prakash/|title=Bhairavi Prakash \u2013 Amani Institute|website=amaniinstitute.org|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref> \n\n== Career ==\nIn the past, Bhairavi worked as a consultant with Totus Consulting, Chennai, where the work she did focusing on coaching and leadership development projects won awards.<ref name=\":0\" /> Bhairavi set up India's first for-profit school-mental health program.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n\n== Social Entrepreneurship ==\nBhairavi founded The Mithra Trust in September 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Adlakha|first=Nidhi|url=https://www.thehindu.com/life-and-style/what-mental-health-experts-say/article31185530.ece|title=COVID-19 lockdown: What mental health experts say|date=2020-03-27|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-25|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://projectkal.org/our-voice/2020/1/13/social-entrepreneur-spotlight|title=Social Entrepreneur Spotlight|website=Project Kal|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref> The trust operates as a non-profit that works with various communities on positive mental health through making information available through workshops, tools, and allied services.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.edexlive.com/happening/2019/oct/31/feeling-meh-this-self-help-kit-will-coach-you-on-what-to-say-when-8845.html|title=Feeling meh? This self-help kit will coach you on what to say when|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref> Through The Mithra Trust, Bhairavi created \u201cThe Meh Kit\u201d which serves as a [[self-help]] kit to help people coping with [[Depression (mood)|depression]].<ref name=\":1\" /> <ref>{{Cite news|last=Lazarus|first=Susanna Myrtle|url=https://www.thehindu.com/sci-tech/technology/internet/beat-the-blues-with-these-helpful-kits/article29416688.ece|title=Beat the blues with these helpful kits|date=2019-09-14|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-25|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n\n\n\n<br />\n[[Category:Indian social entrepreneurs]]\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Social entrepreneurs]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian businesswomen]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Indian businesswomen by state or union territory]]\n[[Category:Mental health by country]]\n[[Category:Mental health activists]]\n[[Category:Psychologists by nationality]]\n[[Category:Indian psychologists]]\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: bachelor\u2019s degree \u2192 bachelor's degree, \u2019s \u2192 's (2)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bhairavi_Prakash"}
{"title_page": "Duane Trucks", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name             = Duane Trucks\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| birth_name       =\n| alias            =\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1988|12|28|mf=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Jacksonville, Florida]], United States\n| death_date       =\n| genre            = [[Blues rock]], [[Southern rock]], [[Jam rock]]\n| occupation       = Musician\n| instrument       = Drums\n| years_active     = 2000s\u2013present\n| label            = \n| associated_acts  = [[Widespread Panic]]<br>[[Hard Working Americans]]<br>[[The Quark Alliance]]<br>[[Col. Bruce Hampton]]\n| website          = \n}}\n\n'''Duane Trucks''' (born December 28, 1988)<ref>{{cite web|title=Screenshot of TTB Facebook Page wishing Duane Trucks a happy birthday on Dec. 28|url=https://s27.postimg.org/5l06i706r/Duane_Trucks_Birthday.jpg|website=Facebook/PostImage|accessdate=2017-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171202203239/https://s27.postimg.org/5l06i706r/Duane_Trucks_Birthday.jpg|archive-date=2017-12-02|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Armonaitis|first1=Dan|title=Duane Trucks talks about a relative who isn\u2019t Derek or Butch, and about a love that isn\u2019t music|url=http://soundobservations.blogs.goupstate.com/10538/|website=Sound Observations|accessdate=2017-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203224446/http://soundobservations.blogs.goupstate.com/10538/|archive-date=2017-12-03|url-status=dead}}</ref> is an American musician best known as the current drummer for [[Widespread Panic]] and [[Hard Working Americans]].\n\n==Life and career==\nDuane Trucks was born on December 28, 1988 in [[Jacksonville, Florida]]. He began learning to play drums at the age of two and was given his first drum kit on his third birthday.<ref name=\"ARTSATL1\">{{cite web|last1=Stepp|first1=Brenda|title=Maker\u2019s Dozen: Widespread Panic\u2019s Duane Trucks carries forward his family legacy|url=http://www.artsatl.com/makers-dozen-widespread-panics-duane-trucks/|website=ARTSATL|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>\n\nHis first foray into being a professional musician was with bands led by [[Col. Bruce Hampton]]. He performed with Hampton in the Pharaoh Gummit beginning in the mid-2000s and became a founding member of one of Hampton's backup bands, [[The Quark Alliance]], in 2007. He became a founding member of '''Flannel Church''', a band that includes fellow Hampton collaborator [[A. J. Ghent]], in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Berndtson|first1=Chad|title=HT INTERVIEW: DUANE TRUCKS \u2013 FLANNEL CHURCH|url=http://www.glidemagazine.com/78757/ht-interview-duane-trucks-flannel-church/|website=Glad Magazine|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> They played a number of festivals including the 2013 [[Wanee Music Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|title=FLANNEL CHURCH - LIVE AT 2013 WANEE MUSIC FESTIVAL|url=http://www.munck-music.com/collections/wanee-music-festival/products/2013-wanee-flannel_church|website=Munck Music Live Recordings|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013 Duane Trucks became a founding member of the [[Supergroup (music)|supergroup]] [[Hard Working Americans]] which also features [[Dave Schools]], [[Todd Snider]] and [[Neal Casal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Hard Working Americans: Todd Snider, Dave Schools, Neal Casal, Duane Trucks and Chad Staehly|url=http://www.jambands.com/news/2013/09/19/hard-working-americans-todd-snider-dave-schools-neal-casal-duane-trucks-and-chad-staehly/|website=jambands.com|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> He began filling in for founding [[Widespread Panic]] drummer [[Todd Nance]] in late 2014 when Nance stepped away from the band to deal with personal matters. He continued performing with the band as a fill in musician until February 2016 when it was announced that he would be replacing Nance as the band's official drummer.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bernstein|first1=Scott|title=Duane Trucks Has Replaced Todd Nance In Widespread Panic|url=http://www.jambase.com/article/duane-trucks-has-replaced-todd-nance-in-widespread-panic|website=JamBase|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> Despite not having been an official member of the band at the time, Trucks recorded all of the drum parts on Widespread Panic's 2015 album ''[[Street Dogs (Widespread Panic album)|Street Dogs]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Street Dogs AllMusic|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/street-dogs-mw0002863470/credits|website=AllMusic|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nTrucks comes from [[Trucks family|a musical family]]; his uncle was [[Allman Brothers Band]] drummer [[Butch Trucks]] and his older brother is [[Derek Trucks]] who is a former member of the Allman Brothers Band and currently performs with the [[Tedeschi Trucks Band]].<ref name=\"ARTSATL1\"/> He is the great nephew of MLB pitcher [[Virgil Trucks]].\n\nHe is married to Cameron Herring, the daughter of his Widespread Panic bandmate [[Jimmy Herring]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stepp|first1=Brenda|title=Q&A: Widespread Panic\u2019s gentle guitar giant Jimmy Herring on his music and achieving balance|url=http://www.artsatl.com/qa-widespread-panics-jimmy-herring-guitars-life-road/|website=ARTSATL|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Hudson|first1=Phil|title=Q&A with Jimmy Herring of Widespread Panic (SLIDESHOW)|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/atlanta/news/2015/10/20/q-a-with-jimmy-herring-of-widespread-panic.html|website=Atlanta Business Chronicle|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.widespreadpanic.com/ Widespread Panic Official Website]\n*[http://www.thehardworkingamericans.com/ Hard Working Americans Official Website]\n\n{{Widespread Panic}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Trucks, Duane}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Widespread Panic members]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Jacksonville, Florida]]\n[[Category:American drummers]]\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American drummers]]\n[[Category:Hard Working Americans members]]\n[[Category:Trucks family]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name             = Duane Trucks\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| birth_name       =\n| alias            =\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1988|12|28|mf=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Jacksonville, Florida]], United States\n| death_date       =\n| genre            = [[Blues rock]], [[Southern rock]], [[Jam rock]]\n| occupation       = Musician\n| instrument       = Drums\n| years_active     = 2000s\u2013present\n| label            = \n| associated_acts  = [[Widespread Panic]]<br>[[Hard Working Americans]]<br>[[The Quark Alliance]]<br>[[Col. Bruce Hampton]]\n| website          = \n}}\n\n'''Duane Trucks''' (born December 28, 1988)<ref>{{cite web|title=Screenshot of TTB Facebook Page wishing Duane Trucks a happy birthday on Dec. 28|url=https://s27.postimg.org/5l06i706r/Duane_Trucks_Birthday.jpg|website=Facebook/PostImage|accessdate=2017-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171202203239/https://s27.postimg.org/5l06i706r/Duane_Trucks_Birthday.jpg|archive-date=2017-12-02|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Armonaitis|first1=Dan|title=Duane Trucks talks about a relative who isn\u2019t Derek or Butch, and about a love that isn\u2019t music|url=http://soundobservations.blogs.goupstate.com/10538/|website=Sound Observations|accessdate=2017-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203224446/http://soundobservations.blogs.goupstate.com/10538/|archive-date=2017-12-03|url-status=dead}}</ref> is an American musician best known as the current drummer for [[Widespread Panic]] and [[Hard Working Americans]].\n\n==Life and career==\nDuane Trucks was born on December 28, 1988 in [[Jacksonville, Florida]]. He began learning to play drums at the age of two and was given his first drum kit on his third birthday.<ref name=\"ARTSATL1\">{{cite web|last1=Stepp|first1=Brenda|title=Maker\u2019s Dozen: Widespread Panic\u2019s Duane Trucks carries forward his family legacy|url=http://www.artsatl.com/makers-dozen-widespread-panics-duane-trucks/|website=ARTSATL|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>\n\nHis first foray into being a professional musician was with bands led by [[Col. Bruce Hampton]]. He performed with Hampton in the Pharaoh Gummit beginning in the mid-2000s and became a founding member of one of Hampton's backup bands, [[The Quark Alliance]], in 2007. He became a founding member of '''Flannel Church''', a band that includes fellow Hampton collaborator [[A. J. Ghent]], in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Berndtson|first1=Chad|title=HT INTERVIEW: DUANE TRUCKS \u2013 FLANNEL CHURCH|url=http://www.glidemagazine.com/78757/ht-interview-duane-trucks-flannel-church/|website=Glad Magazine|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> They played a number of festivals including the 2013 [[Wanee Music Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|title=FLANNEL CHURCH - LIVE AT 2013 WANEE MUSIC FESTIVAL|url=http://www.munck-music.com/collections/wanee-music-festival/products/2013-wanee-flannel_church|website=Munck Music Live Recordings|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013 Duane Trucks became a founding member of the [[Supergroup (music)|supergroup]] [[Hard Working Americans]] which also features [[Dave Schools]], [[Todd Snider]] and [[Neal Casal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Hard Working Americans: Todd Snider, Dave Schools, Neal Casal, Duane Trucks and Chad Staehly|url=http://www.jambands.com/news/2013/09/19/hard-working-americans-todd-snider-dave-schools-neal-casal-duane-trucks-and-chad-staehly/|website=jambands.com|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> He began filling in for founding [[Widespread Panic]] drummer [[Todd Nance]] in late 2014 when Nance stepped away from the band to deal with personal matters. He continued performing with the band as a fill in musician until February 2016 when it was announced that he would be replacing Nance as the band's official drummer.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bernstein|first1=Scott|title=Duane Trucks Has Replaced Todd Nance In Widespread Panic|url=http://www.jambase.com/article/duane-trucks-has-replaced-todd-nance-in-widespread-panic|website=JamBase|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> Despite not having been an official member of the band at the time, Trucks recorded all of the drum parts on Widespread Panic's 2015 album ''[[Street Dogs (Widespread Panic album)|Street Dogs]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Street Dogs AllMusic|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/street-dogs-mw0002863470/credits|website=AllMusic|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nTrucks comes from [[Trucks family|a musical family]]; his uncle was [[Allman Brothers Band]] drummer [[Butch Trucks]] and his older brother is [[Derek Trucks]] who is a former member of the Allman Brothers Band and currently performs with the [[Tedeschi Trucks Band]].<ref name=\"ARTSATL1\"/> He is the great nephew of MLB pitcher [[Virgil Trucks]].\n\nHe is married to Cameron Herring, the daughter of his Widespread Panic band mate [[Jimmy Herring]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stepp|first1=Brenda|title=Q&A: Widespread Panic\u2019s gentle guitar giant Jimmy Herring on his music and achieving balance|url=http://www.artsatl.com/qa-widespread-panics-jimmy-herring-guitars-life-road/|website=ARTSATL|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Hudson|first1=Phil|title=Q&A with Jimmy Herring of Widespread Panic (SLIDESHOW)|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/atlanta/news/2015/10/20/q-a-with-jimmy-herring-of-widespread-panic.html|website=Atlanta Business Chronicle|accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.widespreadpanic.com/ Widespread Panic Official Website]\n*[http://www.thehardworkingamericans.com/ Hard Working Americans Official Website]\n\n{{Widespread Panic}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT: